commentary: de Silva to Waller, no run in the slot to be hit, but finds the bowler's hands once again. Full and on middle and the batsman gives it a mighty slog. But he can't get past the bowler

commentary: de Silva to Waller, FOUR runs a crucial boundary! The batsman waits for the ball that pitches on middle and angles himself towards the leg side just a little bit. He then opens the bats face and paddles the ball in the air on the leg side. He keeps the shot fine, and the fine leg fielder is too square to get to that.

commentary: Sandakan to Ervine, FOUR runs and that's the winning runs!, he brings out the paddle reverse sweep and plays it fine once again, races away to the boundary and Zimbabwe tie the five-match series 2-2. This series will be decided on the final match-day.
